tonio Ferrua, \u003Ci>Note e giunte alle iscrizioni cristiane antiche della Sicilia\u003C/i> (Vatican, 1989)\u003C/span>",{"type":175,"bibl":176},"discussion",[50],"\u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#martaf #AA\">\n  \u003Cab>\n    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>Σωκράτης\u003C/name>\u003C/persName>\n    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cg ref=\"#christogram\">☧\u003C/g> \u003Cw>πάντων\u003C/w> \u003Cw>ὁ\u003C/w> \u003Cg ref=\"#christogram\">☧\u003C/g>\n    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003Cw>φίλος\u003C/w> \u003Cw>ἐνθά\n    \u003Clb n=\"4\" break=\"no\"/>δε\u003C/w> \u003Cw>κεῖται\u003C/w>\n  \u003C/ab>\n\u003C/div>",{"n":94,"url":95,"height":96,"width":97,"desc":98,"surfaceType":99},[],[134,146,165],[131,141,147,162,172],[135,148,166],[184,185,4,19,24,28,186,187,188,189,187,190,191,118],"isic001626","epitaph for sokrates","catina","catania","italy","sicily","museo civico di catania","ancient greek",{"title":193,"body":194,"divs":195,"images":216},"ISic001626. Epitaph for Sokrates","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Σωκράτης \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>christogram πάντων ὁ christogram \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>φίλος ἐνθά-\u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>δε κεῖται \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΣΩΚΡΑΤΗΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>christogramΠΑΝΤΩΝΟchristogram\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΦΙΛΟΣΕΝΘΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΔΕΚΕΙΤΑΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001626_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001626_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001626.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001626-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Orsi, Agnello, Wessel: πάντων ὁ | φίλος; Ferrua, Korhonen: πάντων | φίλος (Ο is part of the Christogram)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Sokrates, the friend of all, lies here.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Sokrates, l’amico di tutti, giace qui.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This epitaph has a formula very similar to pagan epitaphs, although the presence of the two Christograms denotes it as Christian. Ferrua and Korhonen read \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">πάντων φίλος\u003C/span> with the interpretation of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ο\u003C/span> as part of the Christogram, which in this case should be interpreted as \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ Χ(ριστό)ς\u003C/span> (the same hight of the letter \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">O\u003C/span> compared to the other letters of the text is probably a misinterpretation of the stonecutter). However, there is no need to eliminate the article since other parallels of similar epithets denoting friendship and affection in Christian inscriptions, such as IMusCatania 178 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001359\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001359\u003C/a> and SEG 65. 791 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001633\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001633\u003C/a> present the names of the deceased followed by adjectives preceded by the article (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Κάλλιστος καὶ | Εὐκαρπία οἱ φιλόστορ|γοι\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ πανφίλ|ητος ... Εὐδέμων\u003C/span> respectively).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 196 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Agnello 1953 no.58) \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1918 62 no.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 1022 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000394\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrua 1989 110 no.416 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001995\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[196,199,202,205,207,210,213],{"id":197,"html":198},"editions","\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Σωκράτης \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>christogram πάντων ὁ christogram \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>φίλος ἐνθά-\u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>δε κεῖται \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΣΩΚΡΑΤΗΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>christogramΠΑΝΤΩΝΟchristogram\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΦΙΛΟΣΕΝΘΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΔΕΚΕΙΤΑΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":200,"html":201},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Orsi, Agnello, Wessel: πάντων ὁ | φίλος; Ferrua, Korhonen: πάντων | φίλος (Ο is part of the Christogram)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":203,"html":204},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Sokrates, the friend of all, lies here.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":203,"html":206},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Sokrates, l’amico di tutti, giace qui.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":208,"html":209},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>This epitaph has a formula very similar to pagan epitaphs, although the presence of the two Christograms denotes it as Christian. Ferrua and Korhonen read \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">πάντων φίλος\u003C/span> with the interpretation of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ο\u003C/span> as part of the Christogram, which in this case should be interpreted as \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ Χ(ριστό)ς\u003C/span> (the same hight of the letter \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">O\u003C/span> compared to the other letters of the text is probably a misinterpretation of the stonecutter). However, there is no need to eliminate the article since other parallels of similar epithets denoting friendship and affection in Christian inscriptions, such as IMusCatania 178 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001359\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001359\u003C/a> and SEG 65. 791 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001633\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001633\u003C/a> present the names of the deceased followed by adjectives preceded by the article (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Κάλλιστος καὶ | Εὐκαρπία οἱ φιλόστορ|γοι\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ὁ πανφίλ|ητος ... Εὐδέμων\u003C/span> respectively).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":211,"html":212},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 196 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Agnello 1953 no.58) \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002211\" targ